  volume = {164},
  annote = {This paper explores how virtual humans' head-nodding behavior in VR affects participants’ perceptions of interaction quality, trust, and engagement. Participants rated the nodding virtual character much higher for maintaining eye contact and showing attention to what was being said. It helped enhance immersion. Participants were also more likely to approach a nodding virtual character than a non-nodding one. As for limitations, the authors suggest expanding participant demographics, refining nodding animations, and exploring VR applications in education.},
